Access.description:
The ``access`` block contains information related to access control for
this data object.
Access.title: Access

Aggregation.description:
The ``fmu.aggregation`` block contains information about an aggregation
performed over an ensemble.
Aggregation.title: Aggregation

AnyData.description:
The ``data`` block contains information about the data contained in this object.
This class, ``AnyData``, is a root model that allows for data with more specific
content types to be placed within it. It can contain the metadata for any data
object.

See :class:`Data` to get an overview of all of the subfields used in the ``data``
block. Between the different content types, only the ``data.content`` field will
differ. This field indicates the type of content the data are representing.
AnyData.title: AnyData

AnyStandardResult.description:
The ``standard result`` field contains information about which standard result this
data object represents. Data that is tagged as such is a standard result from FMU
that conforms to a specified standard.

This class, ``AnyStandardResult``, acts as a container for different standard
results, with the exact standard result being identified by the
``standard_result.name`` field.
AnyStandardResult.title: AnyStandardResult

Asset.description:
The ``access.asset`` block contains information about the owner asset of
these data.
Asset.title: Asset

AxisOrientation.description: The axis orientation for a given data object.
AxisOrientation.title: AxisOrientation

BoundingBox2D.description: Contains the 2D coordinates within which a data object is contained.
BoundingBox2D.title: BoundingBox2D

BoundingBox3D.description: Contains the 3D coordinates within which a data object is contained.
BoundingBox3D.title: BoundingBox3D

CPGridPropertySpecification.description: Specifies relevant values describing a corner point grid property object.
CPGridPropertySpecification.title: CPGridPropertySpecification

CPGridSpecification.description: Specifies relevant values describing a corner point grid object.
CPGridSpecification.title: CPGridSpecification

Case.description:
The ``fmu.case`` block contains information about the case from which this data
object was exported.

A case represent a set of ensembles that belong together, either by being part of
the same run (i.e. history matching) or by being placed together by the user,
corresponding to /scratch/<asset>/<user>/<my case name>/.

.. note:: If an FMU data object is exported outside the case context, this block
   will not be present.
Case.title: Case

CaseMetadata.description:
The FMU metadata model for an FMU case.

A case represent a set of iterations that belong together, either by being part of
the same run (i.e. history matching) or by being placed together by the user,
corresponding to /scratch/<asset>/<user>/<my case name>/.
CaseMetadata.title: CaseMetadata

Classification.description: The security classification for a given data object.
Classification.title: Classification

Context.description:
The ``fmu.context`` block contains the FMU context in which this data object
was produced.
Context.title: Context

CoordinateSystem.description:
The ``masterdata.smda.coordinate_system`` block contains the coordinate
system known to SMDA.
CoordinateSystem.title: CoordinateSystem

CountryItem.description:
A single country in the ``smda.masterdata.country`` list of countries
known to SMDA.
CountryItem.title: CountryItem

CubeSpecification.description: Specifies relevant values describing a cube object, i.e. a seismic cube.
CubeSpecification.title: CubeSpecification

DepthData.description:
The ``data`` block contains information about the data contained in this object.
This class contains metadata for depth type.
DepthData.title: DepthData

DiscoveryItem.description:
A single discovery in the ``masterdata.smda.discovery`` list of discoveries
known to SMDA.
DiscoveryItem.title: DiscoveryItem

Display.description:
The ``display`` block contains information related to how this data object
should/could be displayed. As a general rule, the consumer of data is responsible
for figuring out how a specific data object shall be displayed. However, we use
this block to communicate preferences from the data producers perspective.

We also maintain this block due to legacy reasons. No data filtering logic should
be placed on the ``display`` block.
Display.title: Display

Ensemble.description:
The ``fmu.ensemble`` block contains information about the ensemble this data
object belongs to.
Ensemble.title: Ensemble

EnsembleContext.description:
The ``fmu.context`` block contains the FMU context in which this data object
was produced. Here ``stage`` is required to be ``ensemble``.
EnsembleContext.title: EnsembleContext

EnsembleMetadata.description:
The FMU metadata model for an FMU ensemble.

An object representing a single Ensemble of a specific case.
EnsembleMetadata.title: EnsembleMetadata

Entity.description:
The ``fmu.entity`` block identifies data objects representing the same entity
within a case, i.e. both realizations and aggregations of a particular entity
will share the same unique identifier.
Entity.title: Entity

Ert.description: The ``fmu.ert`` block contains information about the current ert run.
Ert.title: Ert

ErtSimulationMode.description:
The simulation mode ert was run in. These definitions come from
`ert.mode_definitions`.
ErtSimulationMode.title: ErtSimulationMode

Experiment.description:
The ``fmu.ert.experiment`` block contains information about
the current ert experiment run.
Experiment.title: Experiment

FMU.description:
The ``fmu`` block contains all attributes specific to FMU. The idea is that the FMU
results data model can be applied to data from *other* sources - in which the
fmu-specific stuff may not make sense or be applicable.
FMU.title: FMU

FMUBase.description:
The ``fmu`` block contains all attributes specific to FMU. The idea is that the FMU
results data model can be applied to data from *other* sources - in which the
fmu-specific stuff may not make sense or be applicable.
FMUBase.title: FMUBase

FMUContext.description: The context in which FMU was being run when data were generated.
FMUContext.title: FMUContext

FMUEnsemble.description:
The ``fmu`` block contains all attributes specific to FMU. The idea is that the FMU
results data model can be applied to data from *other* sources - in which the
fmu-specific stuff may not make sense or be applicable.
This is a specialization of the FMU block for ``ensemble`` objects.
FMUEnsemble.title: FMUEnsemble

FMURealization.description:
The ``fmu`` block contains all attributes specific to FMU. The idea is that the FMU
results data model can be applied to data from *other* sources - in which the
fmu-specific stuff may not make sense or be applicable.
This is a specialization of the FMU block for ``realization`` objects.
FMURealization.title: FMURealization

File.description:
The ``file`` block contains references to this data object as a file on a disk.
A filename in this context can be actual, or abstract. Particularly the
``relative_path`` is, and will most likely remain, an important identifier for
individual file objects within an FMU case - irrespective of the existance of an
actual file system. For this reason, the ``relative_path`` - as well as the
``checksum_md5`` will be generated even if a file is not saved to disk. The
``absolute_path`` will only be generated in the case of actually creating a file on
disk and is not required under this schema.
File.title: File

FileFormat.description: The format of a given data object.

FileSchema.description: The schema identifying the format of a standard result.
FileSchema.title: FileSchema

Workflow.description:
The ``fmu.workflow`` block refers to specific subworkflows within the large

programmatic access to the workflows being run in important software within FMU.

.. note:: A key usage of ``fmu.workflow.reference`` is related to ensuring
   uniqueness of data objects.
Workflow.title: Workflow
